-country]], [[american football|football]], [[golf]], [[ice hockey]], [[lacrosse]], [[skiing|ski]], [[soccer]], [[swimming (sport)|swimming]], [[tennis]], [[track & field|track]] and [[scholastic wrestling|wrestling]].\n\n==Girls CHSL Divisions==\nDivisional alignments may vary from sport to sport, depending upon the number of schools participating in the sport and the enrollment of those participating schools. Listed below are typical divisional alignments for a common sport, in this case girls basketball (as of April, 2015).<ref name=\"chsl.com\"/>\n\n===Central Division===\n* Bloomfield Hills Marian\n* Dearborn Divine Child\n* Farmington Hills Mercy\n* Warren Regina\n\n===AA Division===\n* Allen Park Cabrini \n* Ann Arbor Father Gabriel Richard\n* Macomb Lutheran North \n* Pontiac Notre Dame Preparatory \n* Riverview Gabriel Richard\n\n===East Division===\n* Clarkston Everest Collegiate\n* Bloomfield Hills Cranbrook-Kingswood\n* Madison Heights Bishop Foley Catholic\n* Marine City Cardinal Mooney Catholic\n* Royal Oak Shrine Catholic\n* Waterford Our Lady of the Lakes\n* Wixom St. Catherine of Siena Academy\n\n===West Division===\n* Bloomfield Hills Academy of the Sacred Heart\n* Detroit Cristo Rey \n* Macomb Austin Catholic \n* West Bloomfield Frankel Jewish Academy\n\n==Boys CHSL Divisions==\n\nDivisional alignments may vary from sport to sport, depending upon the number of schools participating in the sport and the enrollment of those participating schools. Listed below are typical divisional alignments for a common sport, in this case boys basketball (as of April, 2015).<ref name=\"chsl.com\"/>\n\n===Central Division===\n\n* Bloomfield Hills Brother Rice \n* Detroit Catholic Central\n* University of Detroit Jesuit \n* Orchard Lake St. Mary's Preparatory \n* Warren De La Salle Collegiate\n\n===AA Division===\n* Ann Arbor Father Gabriel Richard\n* Dearborn Divine Child\n* Detroit Loyola\n* Macomb Lutheran North\n\n===Intersectional 1 Division===\n* Allen Park Cabrini\n* Bloomfield Hills Cranbrook-Kingswood \n* Madison Heights Bishop Foley Catholic\n* Royal Oak Shrine Catholic\n* Waterford Our Lady of the Lakes\n\n===Intersectional 2 Division===\n* Clarkston Everest Catholic\n* Detroit Cristo Rey \n* Macomb Austin Catholic \n* Marine City Cardinal Mooney Catholic\n* Riverview Gabriel Richard\n* West Bloomfield Frankel Jewish Academy\n\n==Former League Members (closed schools)==\n<ref>http://dignitas.typepad.com/.a/6a00d8341f704253ef015436db7206970c-800wi</ref><ref>http://www.bishopgallagher.org/2011/11/list-of-closed-detroit-area-catholic-high-schools.html</ref><ref>http://michigan-football.com/f/totalcounties.htm</ref><ref>http://creativegene.blogspot.com/2007/03/felician-sisters-in-michigan-part-3-of.html</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! colspan=8|Catholic High School League\n|-\n! School !! Location !! Final Enrollment !! Class !! Nickname !! Colors      !! Gender !! Years\n|-\n| [[Academy of the Sacred Heart (Grosse Pointe Farms, Michigan)|Academy of the Sacred Heart]] || [[Grosse Pointe Farms, Michigan|Grosse Pointe Farms]], [[Wayne County, Michigan|Wayne County]] ||  || || || Blue and White (color)|{{color box|blue}}{{color box|white}} <small>Blue & White</small>  || All-Girls|| 1887-1969\n|-\n| [[All Saints High School (Detroit, Michigan)|All Saints High School]] || [[Detroit]], [[Wayne County, Michigan|Wayne County]] || 68 || C-D || Saints || Green and White (color)|{{color box|green}}{{color box|white}} <small>Green & White</small>   || Coed|| 1922-1970\n|-\n| [[Anchor Bay Catholic High School (Michigan)|Anchor Bay Catholic High School]] || [[New Baltimore, Michigan|New Baltimore]], [[Macomb County, Michigan|Macomb County]] ||  || D || Giants || Red and White (color)|{{color box|red}}{{color box|white}} <small>Red & White</small>  || || Closed 1970\n|-\n| [[Annunciation High School (Detroit)|Annunciation High School]] || [[Detroit]], [[Wayne County, Michigan|Wayne County]] ||  || C || Cougars || Blu