ord Rustics]] played in seven Goodfellow Games, the most among Detroit Parochial League schools.\n*The [[St. Ambrose High School (Grosse Pointe, Michigan)|Grosse Pointe St. Ambrose Cavaliers]] and the [[Detroit Catholic Central High School|Detroit Catholic Central Shamrocks]] won the most Goodfellow Games with five each.  The [[Denby High School|Detroit Denby Tars]] won four Goodfellow Games, the most among Detroit City League schools.<ref>football.com/f/detrotcc.htm</ref><ref name=\"michigan\">http://michigan-</ref><ref name=\"michigan\"/><ref>football.com/f/dambrose.htm</ref><ref>http://michigan-football.com/f/detdenby.htm</ref><ref>http://michigan-football.com/f/dtstther.htm</ref><ref>http://michigan-football.com/f/rivlourd.htm</ref> \n*[[St. Ambrose High School (Grosse Pointe, Michigan)|The Grosse Pointe St. Ambrose Cavaliers]] had the most Goodfellow Game shutouts with three, while the [[Denby High School|Detroit Denby Tars]] had the most tied Goodfellow Games with two.<ref>http://michigan-football.com/f/drdchild.htm</ref><ref>http://michigan-football.com/f/hamtrmck.htm</ref><ref>http://michigan-football.com/f/dhredeem.htm</ref><ref>http://michigan-football.com/f/danthony.htm</ref><ref>http://michigan-football.com/f/rdstmary.htm</ref><ref>http://michigan-football.com/f/dtstgreg.htm</ref><ref>http://michigan-football.com/f/hwndame.htm</ref>\n*The [[University of Detroit Jesuit High School and Academy|University of Detroit High Cubs]] played in three Goodfellows Games, all representing the Detroit City League, before joining the Detroit Parochial League in 1958.<ref>http://michigan-football.com/f/udjesuit.htm</ref>\n*The Goodfellow Game regularly drew crowds of 40,000 spectators at its peak in the late 1950s and early 1960s.<ref name=\"detroitathletic.com\"/>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! colspan=3|The Goodfellow Game\n|-\n! Year !! Winning League !! Game Results \n|-\n| 1938 || Parochial League ||Detroit Catholic Central Shamrocks 19, [[Hamtramck Hig