oit Southeastern]] Jungaleers 6\n|- \n|1958 || City League || Detroit Redford Huskies 27, Detroit St. Mary of Redford Rustics 7\n|-\n|1959 || Parochial League || Grosse Pointe St. Ambrose Cavaliers 13, Detroit Cooley Cardinals 7\n|-\n|1960 || City League || Detroit Denby Tars 21, Detroit Catholic Central Shamrocks 18\n|-\n|1961 || Parochial League || Grosse Pointe St.  Ambrose Cavaliers 20, Detroit Pershing Doughboys 0\n|- \n|1962 || Parochial League || Grosse Pointe St. Ambrose Cavaliers 19, Detroit Cooley Cardinals 0\n|-\n|1963 || City League || Detroit Denby Tars 7, Harper Woods Notre Dame Fightin' Irish 0 \n|-\n|1964 || Parochial League || Grosse Pointe St. Ambrose Cavaliers 20, Detroit Southeastern Jungaleers 0\n|-\n|1965 || Tie || Harper Woods Notre Dame Fightin' Irish 14, Detroit Denby Tars 14 \n|- \n|1966 || Parochial League || Grosse Pointe St. Ambrose Cavaliers 33, Detroit Denby Tars 19\n|-\n|1967 || Parochial League || Dearborn Divine Child Falcons 14, Detroit Denby Tars 7\n|}\n\n{{Columns-end}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.chsl.com/ Catholic High School League]\n* [http://www.aodonline.org/CHSL/CHSL.htm Aodonline.org]\n\n[[Category:Michigan high school sports conferences]]\n[[Category:High school sports conferences and leagues in the United States]]\n[[Category:Catholic sports organizations]]\n[[Category:Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Detroit]]\n", "text_old": "The '''Catholic High School League''' (CHSL) is a school athletic conference based in [[Detroit]], [[Michigan]], led by director Victor Michaels. All member schools are also members of the [[Michigan High School Athletic Association]] (MHSAA), the governing body for Michigan scholastic sports. Unlike many similar leagues, the CHSL governs secondary, middle, and elementary sports for most of the parochial schools in the Detroit area. Most league schools are Catholic, but there are other religious denominations as well. Every school in the CHSL is a [[private school]]. In 2019, the CHSL council voted to rename the AB/ Division I/II championship to the Bishop division championship, and the CD/ Division III/IV championship to the Cardinal Division championship.{{CN|date=March 2020}}\n\n==Member schools==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! colspan=8|Catholic High School League\n|-\n! School !! Location !! Enrollment<ref>http://www.mhsaa.com/schools/administrators/enrollmentclassification.aspx</ref>!! Class !! Nickname !! Colors      !! Gender  !!  Established\n|-\n| [[Cabrini High School (Allen Park)|Allen Park Cabrini]] || [[Allen Park]], [[Wayne County, Michigan|Wayne County]]  || 265 || C || Monarchs || Blue and Gold (color)|{{color box|blue}}{{color box|gold}} <small>Blue & Gold</small>  || Coed  ||  1960\n|-\n| [[Father Gabriel Richard High School (Ann Arbor, Michigan)|Ann Arbor Father Gabriel Richard]] || [[Ann Arbor, Michigan|Ann Arbor]], [[Washtenaw County, Michigan|Washtenaw County]] || 536 || B || Fighting Irish ||Green and White (color)|{{color box|green}}{{color box|white}} <small>Green & White</small>   || Coed  ||  1980\n|-\n| [[Greenhills School|Ann Arbor Greenhills]] || [[Ann Arbor, Michigan|Ann Arbor]], [[Washtenaw County, Michigan|Washtenaw County]] || 318 || C || Gryphons ||Navy and Green (color)|{{color box|navy}}{{color box|green}} <small>Navy & Green</small>   || Coed  ||  1969\n|-\n| [[Brother Rice High School (Michigan)|Bloomfield Hills Brother Rice]] || [[Bloomfield Township, Oakland County, Michigan|Bloomfield Twp]], [[Oakland County, Michigan|Oakland County]]|| 564 || A || Warriors || Black and Orange (color)|{{color box|black}}{{color box|orange}} <small>Black & Orange</small>  || All-Boys  ||  1960\n|-\n| [[Academy of the Sacred Heart (Bloomfield Township, Michigan)|Bloomfield Hills Academy of the Sacred Heart]] || [[Bloomfield Township, Oakland County, Michigan|Bloomfield Twp]], [[Oakland County, Michigan|Oakland County]] || 139 || C || Gazelles || Navy Blue and Gold (color)| {{color bo